 including George and Ira Gershwin, Irving Berlin, Jerome Kern, and Johnny Mercer. He also highlights Astaire’s collaborations with African American musicians and his work with lesser known professionals—arrangers, musicians, dance directors, and performers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDancerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aJazz musicianszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  a1930s movie musicals.  a20th century dance.  a20th century film.  a20th century jazz.  a20th century musicals.  a20th century.  aafrican american musicians.  aamerican choreographers.  aamerican film.  aamerican jazz.  aamerican music culture.  aamerican musicians.  adance.  aeaster parade.  afunny face.  ageorge gershwin.  ahistory of film.  ahistory of jazz.  ahistory of music.  airving berlin.  ajazz and blues.  ajazz icons.  ajazz musician biographies.  ajerome kern.  ajohnny mercer.  amusic and dance.  amusic and race.  amusic legends.  amusicians.  aperforming arts.  atop hat.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026890640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095006140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950061423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520950061/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY